Subject:  mud.el

FWIW, my mud-mcp.el works for Emacs 24.  To be sure, the code is mostly about implementing a MCP 2.1 interface [and thus pointless for LambdaMOO] but there are about 100 lines of code down at the end (scroll down to "comint.el support ... el cheapo mud.el") that implement a mud mode on top of comint (which I did because I got tired of dealing with the idiosyncracies of mud.el and also comint was sort of the "modern" way to do things 13 years ago).  Anyway, that's all here if you just want to get up and running in Emacs 24:

  http://www.ipomoea.org/mcp  

scroll down to "Emacs Lisp"; the first file (mud-mcp.el) suffices, though if you connect to Waterpoint or other such places then you'll want the other two.  And then it's M-x mud-mcp-connect, which creates a comint mode buffer, and as long as you have done a 

   (defconst mud-sites '("LambdaMOO" MOO "lambda.moo.mud.org" 8888) ...)

somewhere, just as for mud.el, you're off to the races.  
